---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="All Career Decision Tools | Econified" description="Directory of our thematic tool hubs for salary, freelance, job offers, and remote work." canonicalUrl="https://econified.com/tools/">
  <main class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumb" style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <a href="/" style="color: inherit;">Home</a> &rsaquo; Tools
    </nav>
    <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <h1>Career Decision Tools</h1>
      <p class="lead">Select a category below to explore our interactive calculators and comparison engines. Every tool runs locally in your browser to guarantee your privacy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="margin-bottom: 3rem; line-height: 1.7;">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Making Career Decisions With Numbers, Not Gut Feelings</h2>
      <p>Most career decisions come down to money, but the math is rarely straightforward. A job offer with a higher base salary can be worth less than one with better benefits. A freelance rate that looks generous can leave you worse off than employment after taxes and downtime. A shorter commute can be worth more than a raise.</p>
      <p>Econified's tools are designed to reveal these hidden trade-offs. Each calculator isolates one piece of the career economics puzzle and lets you adjust assumptions to match your real situation. No accounts, no data collection — every calculation runs entirely in your browser.</p>

      <h3>Which Category Should You Start With?</h3>
      <p>Your starting point depends on the decision you are facing right now:</p>
      <ul style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <li><strong>You have a number and need it in a different format</strong> — Start with <a href="/tools/salary-conversion/">Salary Conversion Tools</a>. These handle the arithmetic of translating between hourly, daily, weekly, biweekly, monthly, and annual pay.</li>
        <li><strong>You are considering freelancing or contracting</strong> — Start with <a href="/tools/contractor-freelance/">Contractor & Freelance Economics</a>. These tools calculate the rate you actually need to charge, factoring in taxes, benefits you would lose, and income gaps between projects.</li>
        <li><strong>You are comparing two or more job offers</strong> — Start with <a href="/tools/job-offer-decisions/">Job Offer & Compensation Decisions</a>. These tools help you compare total compensation packages including PTO value, promotion potential, and burnout risk.</li>
        <li><strong>You are weighing remote work against office work</strong> — Start with <a href="/tools/remote-work-economics/">Remote Work & Commute Economics</a>. These tools calculate the true cost of commuting and whether a lower remote salary is actually the better deal.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How the Tools Fit Together</h3>
      <p>Career decisions are rarely isolated. A job switch involves salary conversion, offer comparison, and possibly a commute change all at once. That is why Econified's tools are linked in decision pathways — each tool suggests logical next steps based on what you just calculated. You can follow these pathways or jump directly to any tool that fits your question.</p>
      <p>If you prefer to understand the theory first, our <a href="/guides/">career economics guides</a> provide the mathematical frameworks behind the tools, complete with worked examples and real-world benchmarks.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Explore by Category</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(350px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">
      
      <!-- Salary Conversion -->
      <a href="/tools/salary-conversion/" class="glass-panel" style="display: block; text-decoration: none;">
        <h2 style="color: var(--accent-light); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem;">Salary Conversion Tools</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Standard conversion calculators mapping hourly, daily, and annual compensation.</p>
      </a>

      <!-- Contractor & Freelance -->
      <a href="/tools/contractor-freelance/" class="glass-panel" style="display: block; text-decoration: none;">
        <h2 style="color: var(--accent-light); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem;">Contractor & Freelance Economics</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Tools to evaluate the risk, overhead, and income of independent contracting vs full-time employment.</p>
      </a>

      <!-- Job Offer Decisions -->
      <a href="/tools/job-offer-decisions/" class="glass-panel" style="display: block; text-decoration: none;">
        <h2 style="color: var(--accent-light); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem;">Job Offer & Compensation Decisions</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Compare job offers, negotiate salary, and calculate the true monetary value of benefits and promotions.</p>
      </a>

      <!-- Remote Work Economics -->
      <a href="/tools/remote-work-economics/" class="glass-panel" style="display: block; text-decoration: none;">
        <h2 style="color: var(--accent-light); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem;">Remote Work & Commute Economics</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">How much does your commute really cost? Evaluate if remote work pays off despite a lower base salary.</p>
      </a>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
